# Neo4j auth credentials for the docker-compose neo4j service.
#
# Copy this file to ``.env.neo4j`` (gitignored) and fill in the
# real credentials:
#
#   cp .env.neo4j.example .env.neo4j
#
# IMPORTANT — Neo4j 5.x is strict about unknown ``NEO4J_*`` env
# vars. Setting ``NEO4J_USER`` or ``NEO4J_PASSWORD`` here will
# make the container exit 1 at startup because Neo4j reads them
# as server config keys (``USER`` / ``PASSWORD``) and rejects
# them as undeclared settings.
#
# Use ONE of these forms:
#
#   1. Pre-built ``NEO4J_AUTH`` (preferred):
#        NEO4J_AUTH=neo4j/your_password_here
#      This is the only NEO4J_* env var the neo4j container
#      accepts at startup.
#
#   2. The host-side ``NEO4J_USER`` / ``NEO4J_PASSWORD`` pair from
#      the project's ``.env`` is interpolated into NEO4J_AUTH by
#      docker-compose.yml. You don't need to put those names here;
#      leave them in ``.env``.

NEO4J_AUTH=neo4j/REPLACE_ME
